external_knowledge:
- "blooming gardens" metaphorically refers to category sets;
- "flowers" metaphorically represent data points;
- "more than just a single flower" indicates that the category set should have at least two data points.

Threshold value for numerical score: 50;
Textual information refers to text1 and text2 in the data_points table;
Numerical score refers to numerical1 in the data_points table.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT id, name, description 
FROM business_units 
ORDER BY id;

SELECT data_point_id, COUNT(*)
FROM data_point_images
GROUP BY data_point_id;

SELECT category_set_name, foo
FROM category_sets
WHERE foo > TANH(id);

SELECT data_point_id
FROM data_point_images
WHERE data_point_id IN (
    SELECT id
    FROM data_points
);

SELECT id, name
FROM business_units
ORDER BY id ASC;
